 for bestpractices and # Agent Orchestration & Messaging

## Overview
Build a robust orchestration layer for multi-agent coordination within LifeOps, featuring a traceable agent-to-agent messaging system, handoffs, negotiations, alerts, consensus, and scoped shared memory. Provide per-run scoped memory with TTL and governance, a guaranteed-ordered message bus, schema-validated and versioned messages, conflict-resolution rules, human-in-the-loop controls (pause/resume/halt, input injection), explainability metadata, and full run artifacts with an audit trail. Expose two associated pages:
- Run Details Page (page_run_details_010): granular view of a single cron/agent run — inputs, message traces, logs, diffs, artifacts, timing, outcomes, and revert capabilities.
- Agent Trace & Debugger (page_agent_trace_011): visual debugger for agent behavior — conversation graph, scoped memory, variable states, and step-through execution.

---

## Components to Build

1) Agent Orchestration Core (Backend)
- Message Bus
  - Ordered, per-run message delivery guarantees.
  - Publish/subscribe model with per-run namespaces.
  - Message envelopes include: id, runId, senderId, recipientId, timestamp, version, priorMessageId, traceContext, actionType, payload, explainability metadata, and TTL metadata.
- Scoped Shared Memory
  - Per-run, per-scope memory with TTL and governance rules.
  - API to read/write memory with governance constraints; expiration cleanup jobs.
- Message Schema Validation & Versioning
  - Schemas for messages with version field; runtime validation (Ajv or Zod).
  - Compatibility checks for version upgrades; backward-compatible fallback.
- Conflict Resolution Engine
  - Rules: user constraints > safety > deadlines > ROI.
  - Priority queueing, preemption, and deterministic tie-breaking.
- Run Lifecycle
  - Pause, resume, halt, and human-in-the-loop input injection points.
  - Run state machine with idempotent transitions and rollback hooks.
- Explainability Metadata
  - Attach per-message actions, decisions, and rationale; exportable with artifacts.
- Audit Trail & Artifacts
  - Immutable log of all actions, messages, decisions; exportable run artifacts.
- Reversibility
  - Ability to revert actions within a run up to a defined rollback window.

2) APIs & Data Persistence (Backend)
- Run Management
  - Create Run, Pause/Resume/Halt Run, Cancel Run, Get Run Details
- Messaging API
  - SendMessage(runId, envelope), GetMessageTrace(runId), StreamMessages(runId)
- Memory API
  - GetMemory(runId, scope), PutMemory(runId, scope, data, ttl), InvalidateMemory
- Schema & Validation
  - Define JSON schemas for each message type; runtime validation endpoints
- Artifact & Logs API
  - UploadArtifact(runId, artifact), GetArtifacts(runId), ExportRunArtifacts(runId)
- Security & Access
  - Fine-grained permissions per user/role; run-scoped tokens; audit of access

3) Frontend (UI)
- Run Details Page (page_run_details_010)
  - Overview Panel: run status, schedule, target, inputs, constraints, permissions, TTLs.
  - Message Trace: timeline with messages, sender/receiver, version, TTL, explainability notes; click to expand payloads.
  - Logs & Diffs: log viewer with diffs between states, filter by level, search, time range.
  - Artifacts & Reverts: list of generated artifacts with export/download; revert actions for reversible steps.
  - Timing & Outcome: per-step timing, duration, outcomes, success/failure, retry history.
  - Actions: Pause/Resume/Halt, Inject Human Input, Revert Action, Re-run.
  - Debug Export: export trace to JSON/CSV; replay viewer to reproduce run state.
- Agent Trace & Debugger (page_agent_trace_011)
  - Visual Conversation Graph: nodes for agents, edges for messages; edge labels with actionType and payload summary.
  - Scoped Memory Inspector: per-run/memory scope view with TTL and governance info; search/filter.
  - Variable States: inspector for agent-local variables across steps; current vs previous state diff.
  - Step-Through Execution: play/pause controls, step over/into, breakpoints by agent or message type.
  - Explainability Panels: show rationale per action/message with links to artifacts.
  - Performance & Health Indicators: throughput, latency, retries, and safety warnings.

All frontend code must guard against null/undefined values before array operations and when consuming API results:
- Use data ?? [] for Supabase-like results
- Use Array.isArray checks for any array usage
- Initialize useState with proper defaults: useState<T[]>([]) for arrays
- Validate API responses: Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining where accessing nested API response fields
- Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

- UI Frameworks
  - TypeScript + React (Next.js preferred) with robust state management (React Context + useReducer or Zustand).
- Components & Pages
  - RunDetailsPanel: summary of run inputs, target, constraints, and controls.
  - MessageTraceView: chronological trace with expandable messages; show explainability metadata.
  - LogsDiffViewer: display logs with diffs; filtering by level and time.
  - ArtifactsGallery: thumbnails/list with download/export.
  - MemoryInspector: TTL-bound memory per scope; governance display; edit controls with validation.
  - DebuggerGraph: interactive D3/Canvas-based graph showing agent conversations and memory states.
  - StepperRunner: for step-through execution; breakpoints; single-step/continuous play.
  - RevertModal: confirm revert actions with audit details.
  - ApprovalQueue: list of actions requiring human approval with context.
- Data Handling
  - All API responses validated; fallbacks to [] where appropriate.
  - Guard all array methods with (items ?? []).map(...) or similar Array.isArray(item) guards.
- Accessibility & UX
  - Keyboard navigable, high-contrast controls, responsive layouts, consistent spacing per design system.
- Performance
  - Debounced search, pagination/tagination for traces, virtualization for long traces.

### Backend

- Data Models (PostgreSQL or your chosen DB)
  - Runs: id, name, schedule, timeZone, target, inputs JSONB, state (queued, running, paused, completed, failed), constraints JSONB, safetyRails JSONB, retryPolicy JSONB, createdAt, updatedAt.
  - Messages: id, runId, senderId, recipientId, actionType, version, payload JSONB, explainability JSONB, traceId, timestamp, ttl, state (pending, delivered, processed, failed).
  - MemoryScopes: id, runId, scope, tenant, data JSONB, ttl, governance JSONB, createdAt, expiresAt.
  - Artifacts: id, runId, type, name, payloadLocation, createdAt, metadata JSONB.
  - RunsAudit: eventId, runId, type, description, payload JSONB, createdAt.
- APIs
  - POST /runs → create new run with initial configuration
  - GET /runs/{id} → fetch run summary and status
  - POST /runs/{id}/pause | /resume | /halt → lifecycle controls
  - POST /runs/{id}/messages → publish message to bus
  - GET /runs/{id}/trace → message trace
  - GET /runs/{id}/logs → logs with filtering
  - POST /runs/{id}/memory → write memory
  - GET /runs/{id}/memory → read memory
  - POST /runs/{id}/artifacts → store artifact
  - GET /runs/{id}/artifacts → list/download artifacts
  - POST /runs/{id}/revert → revert last reversible action
- Validation & Safety
  - All inputs validated against schemas; undefined/null guarded with defaults
  - Message versioning validated; incompatible versions route to a safe fallback
  - Access control per runs; audit log all API calls
- Conflict Resolution
  - Implement deterministic resolution engine in services/middleware to enforce priority rules on conflicting actions within a run
- Reversibility & Explanations
  - Revert endpoints trigger reversible action hooks; explainability metadata updated on each action

### Integration

- Message Bus Contract
  - Consistent envelope format; per-run namespaces; traceId propagation across agents
- Memory Governance
  - TTL expiration jobs; governance rules enforcement on read/write
- Schema Validation
  - Centralized schema registry; dynamic validators for new message types
- Frontend-Backend Sync
  - Real-time updates via WebSocket or Server-Sent Events for run state, trace, and memory changes
- Data Export
  - Run artifacts export in JSON/CSV with attached explainability metadata

---

## User Experience Flow

1) Master Dashboard launches a cronjob-based orchestration
- User sees list of cronjobs with next run time, status, and quick actions (Pause, Edit, View)
- Selecting a cronjob opens Run Details Page with summary and historical runs

2) Run Lifecycle
- When a run starts, messages are enqueued on the ordered bus
- Agents exchange traceable messages; memory scopes auto-initialized
- User can Pause/Halt or inject human input at governance points
- If conflicts occur, the Conflict Resolution Engine enforces priorities and logs decisions

3) Run Details Page (page_run_details_010)
- View inputs, trace, logs, diffs, artifacts, timing, and outcomes
- Revert reversible actions using RevertModal; confirm with audit trail
- Export run artifacts and trace for offline analysis
- Re-run with adjusted inputs or constraints if permitted

4) Agent Trace & Debugger (page_agent_trace_011)
- Visualize agent conversations and memory scopes
- Step through execution; inspect variables and explainability notes
- Identify bottlenecks, safety alerts, or conflicting decisions
- Save and share debug sessions; export graph state

5) Security & Governance
- All actions are permissioned; approvals queue for actions requiring human review
- Running analytics show throughput, latency, failures, and safety events

---

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models (Schemas)
  - Run: { id, name, schedule, timeZone, target, inputs, constraints, safetyRails, retryPolicy, state, createdAt, updatedAt }
  - Message: { id, runId, senderId, recipientId, actionType, version, payload, explainability, traceId, timestamp, ttl, state }
  - Memory: { id, runId, scope, data, ttl, governance, createdAt, expiresAt }
  - Artifact: { id, runId, type, name, location, metadata, createdAt }
  - Audit: { id, runId, eventType, description, payload, createdAt }
- API Endpoints
  - Runs: POST /runs, GET /runs/{id}, POST /runs/{id}/pause, /resume, /halt
  - Messages: POST /runs/{id}/messages, GET /runs/{id}/trace
  - Memory: POST /runs/{id}/memory, GET /runs/{id}/memory
  - Artifacts: POST /runs/{id}/artifacts, GET /runs/{id}/artifacts
  - Revert: POST /runs/{id}/revert
- Security
  - JWT-based authentication; per-run authorization checks; audit trails
  - Rate limiting on run actions; retry/backoff policies for API resilience
- Validation Rules
  - Use JSON Schemas with strict validation on payloads
  - Validate API inputs and outputs with defensive defaults
  - Ensure all array operations guard against null/undefined as specified

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] End-to-end run orchestration with ordered message bus guarantees and per-run scope memory
- [ ] All API responses and internal data handling guard against null/undefined before array operations
- [ ] Message schemas versioned and validated; older versions gracefully handled
- [ ] Conflict Resolution Engine deterministically enforces user constraints > safety > deadlines > ROI
- [ ] Pause/Resume/Halt functionality and human-in-the-loop injection fully functional
- [ ] Traceable message logs, with exportable run artifacts and audit trail
- [ ] Run Details Page provides inputs, trace, logs, diffs, artifacts, timing, outcomes, and revert actions
- [ ] Agent Trace & Debugger offers a visual graph, scoped memory, variable states, and step-through execution
- [ ] UI adheres to the specified color palette, typography, spacing, and design tokens
- [ ] All components accessible, responsive, and performant with proper error handling

---

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system rigorously:
- Maintain the dark, high-contrast, minimal aesthetic with restrained accents
- Use a 8px baseline grid; gutters 8/16/24/32; sidebar width 220–260px
- Card surfaces: 8–12px radii, subtle borders and shadows, top-edge highlights
- Typography: Inter/SF Pro Display/Roboto; weight hierarchy as stated
- Data Viz: muted gridlines, bold color series from teal/amber/purple palette
- Interaction: smooth 120–200ms transitions; clear affordances for actions; reversible actions clearly signposted

---

## Visual Style Summary (Recap)

- Palette: deep neutrals (#0B0B0C, #151718) with white text and selective accents (#FF3B30, #00C2A8, #FFB020, #8B5CF6)
- Cards: elevated, rounded, gradient-dark surfaces
- Navigation: compact left rail; active state indicators; breadcrumb top bar
- Graphs: minimalistic, high-contrast data lines on dark background
- Components: consistent borders, shadows, and micro-interactions; accessible controls

